Of the latest two reported exceptions:
(1) The ClassCastException when calling getExtensionProperties() is an Engine bug and has been fixed.
(2) The second exception is a bug in the test code. The dataSet's beforeClose function does not check if variable "integer" is null. In the test run, a null "integer" value caused a NullPointerException

	public void beforeClose( IDataSetInstance dataSet, IReportContext reportContext )
	{
		/* get the variable we added earlier from task */
		Integer integer = (Integer) reportContext.getFromTask( "integer" );
		System.out.println( "get" + integer.toString( ) );
	}

Note to finder: Please file new Bugzilla entries for any future issues you discover during the testing of the scripting feature (that are unrelated to issues logged in this bugzilla).
